            {
               "text": "Continuing our studies, we returned to analyzing comparisons, but this time through subtraction. With this new tool, we concluded that if two quantities are truly equal, subtraction indicates that there will be zero difference between them. For example, in a basket containing 5 apples, if we remove 5 apples, 0 apples will remain (**Calculation 2**):",
